trend_summary: From the earliest to the most recent image the island shows steady infill: housing spreads inland from the eastern coast, marinas lengthen, and the main road-bridge is upgraded. Cultivated fields shrink while tree cover modestly increases in the north. Overall built-up area rises but remains a medium-density, predominantly suburban waterfront settlement.
notable_changes: Expansion of waterfront housing estates along the southeastern shoreline.
Lengthening and addition of marina piers, increasing boat berths.
Conversion of central agricultural plots into residential blocks or mixed use.
Widening/realignment of the bridge and its approach roads.
Incremental growth of tree cover in the northern headland and some park creation.
